Kubernetes Daily Usage Commands ‚Äì Interview Ready
1Ô∏è‚É£ Cluster & Nodes
| Purpose                  | Command                             | Notes                                     |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| List nodes               | `kubectl get nodes`                 | Check node status (Ready/NotReady)        |
| Detailed node info       | `kubectl describe node <node-name>` | View resources, taints, labels            |
| Check cluster components | `kubectl get componentstatuses`     | API server, scheduler, controller-manager |

2Ô∏è‚É£ Pods
| Purpose                   | Command                                       | Notes                         |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| List pods                 | `kubectl get pods -A`                         | Across all namespaces         |
| List pods with node info  | `kubectl get pods -o wide`                    | Shows Node, IP                |
| Detailed pod info         | `kubectl describe pod <pod-name>`             | Events, scheduling, probes    |
| Logs (running pod)        | `kubectl logs <pod-name>`                     | For single container          |
| Logs (specific container) | `kubectl logs <pod-name> -c <container-name>` | Multi-container pod           |
| Logs (previous container) | `kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous`          | CrashLoopBackOff debugging    |
| Exec into pod             | `kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash`    | Debug container interactively |

3Ô∏è‚É£ Deployments & ReplicaSets
| Purpose             | Command                                      | Notes                        |
| ------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| List deployments    | `kubectl get deploy`                         | In default namespace         |
| Describe deployment | `kubectl describe deploy <deployment-name>`  | Shows ReplicaSets, events    |
| Scale deployment    | `kubectl scale deploy <name> --replicas=<n>` | Manual scaling               |
| Rollout status      | `kubectl rollout status deploy/<name>`       | Waits for rollout completion |
| Rollback deployment | `kubectl rollout undo deploy/<name>`         | Revert to previous version   |

4Ô∏è‚É£ Services & Networking
| Purpose          | Command                            | Notes                             |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| List services    | `kubectl get svc`                  | ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer |
| Describe service | `kubectl describe svc <svc-name>`  | Check endpoints, ports            |
| Get endpoints    | `kubectl get endpoints <svc-name>` | Shows pods behind service         |

5Ô∏è‚É£ Ingress
| Purpose          | Command                                   | Notes                  |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| List ingress     | `kubectl get ingress`                     | Shows rules, host/path |
| Describe ingress | `kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name>` | Debug routing issues   |

6Ô∏è‚É£ ConfigMaps & Secrets
| Purpose            | Command                                                                    | Notes                     |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| List configmaps    | `kubectl get configmap`                                                    | Default namespace         |
| Describe configmap | `kubectl describe configmap <name>`                                        | Check keys/values         |
| List secrets       | `kubectl get secret`                                                       | Encoded in base64         |
| Describe secret    | `kubectl describe secret <name>`                                           | Metadata only, not values |
| Decode secret      | `kubectl get secret <name> -o jsonpath="{.data.<key>}" \| base64 --decode` | View actual secret        |

7Ô∏è‚É£ Storage (PV / PVC)
| Purpose      | Command                       | Notes                          |
| ------------ | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| List PV      | `kubectl get pv`              | Check capacity, status         |
| List PVC     | `kubectl get pvc`             | Bound / Pending                |
| Describe PVC | `kubectl describe pvc <name>` | Check PV binding & access mode |
8Ô∏è‚É£ HPA (Autoscaling)
| Purpose      | Command                       | Notes                               |
| ------------ | ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| List HPA     | `kubectl get hpa`             | Min / Max replicas, current metrics |
| Describe HPA | `kubectl describe hpa <name>` | Check scaling events                |
| Top pods     | `kubectl top pods`            | Resource usage per pod              |
| Top nodes    | `kubectl top nodes`           | Resource usage per node             |

9Ô∏è‚É£ Scheduling / Nodes
| Purpose         | Command                                                                | Notes                  |
| --------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Cordon node     | `kubectl cordon <node-name>`                                           | Prevent new pods       |
| Drain node      | `kubectl drain <node-name> --ignore-daemonsets --delete-emptydir-data` | Evict pods safely      |
| Uncordon node   | `kubectl uncordon <node-name>`                                         | Allow scheduling again |
| Get node labels | `kubectl get node <node-name> --show-labels`                           | For node affinity      |

üîü Taints & Tolerations
| Purpose          | Command                                                | Notes                           |                       |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| List node taints | `kubectl describe node <node-name>                     | grep -i taint`                  | Check existing taints |
| Add taint        | `kubectl taint nodes <node-name> key=value:NoSchedule` | Prevent pods without toleration |                       |
| Remove taint     | `kubectl taint nodes <node-name> key:NoSchedule-`      | Remove taint                    |                       |

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Namespaces
| Purpose          | Command                                                   | Notes              |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------ |
| List namespaces  | `kubectl get ns`                                          | Check isolation    |
| Create namespace | `kubectl create ns <name>`                                | Logical separation |
| Use namespace    | `kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=<name>` | Switch context     |

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ General / Debug
| Purpose          | Command                                                       | Notes                   |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| Check events     | `kubectl get events -A --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp` | Last actions in cluster |
| Explain resource | `kubectl explain <resource>`                                  | Helpful in interviews   |
| Apply YAML       | `kubectl apply -f <file.yaml>`                                | Create/update resource  |
| Delete resource  | `kubectl delete -f <file.yaml>`                               | Remove resource         |
| Watch resources  | `kubectl get pods -w`                                         | Real-time monitoring    |

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

‚≠ê Interview Tip

Memorize commands in clusters: pods, deployments, services, storage, nodes.
During the interview, explain your steps while using commands:

‚ÄúFirst I describe the pod, then check logs, then verify node resources and service endpoints‚Ä¶‚Äù
